msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (<i lang=\"pli\">pācittiya</i>)"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Ovādavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 24"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "24. Āmisasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on worldly gain"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.58"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.24.1"></a> <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.279"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="548"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadantā lābhino honti "
"cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"At that time the senior monks who instructed the nuns received robe-cloth, "
"almsfood, dwellings, and medicines."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs1.3"
msgid "Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū evaṃ vadanti—"
msgstr "And the monks from the group of six said this about them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs1.4"
msgid ""
"“na bahukatā therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadituṃ; āmisahetu therā bhikkhū "
"bhikkhuniyo ovadantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“The senior monks aren’t instructing the nuns to render a service, but for "
"the sake of worldly gain.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="549"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs1.5"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs1.6"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū evaṃ vakkhanti—"
msgstr "“How can the monks from the group of six say that"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs1.8"
msgid ""
"‘na bahukatā therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadituṃ; āmisahetu therā bhikkhū "
"bhikkhuniyo ovadantī’”ti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"the senior monks aren’t instructing the nuns to render a service, but for "
"the sake of worldly gain?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs1.9"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, evaṃ vadetha—‘"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you say this?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs1.10"
msgid ""
"na bahukatā therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadituṃ; āmisahetu therā bhikkhū "
"bhikkhuniyo ovadantī’”ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs1.12"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs1.13"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, evaṃ vakkhatha—"
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you say that"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs1.14"
msgid ""
"‘na bahukatā therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadituṃ; āmisahetu therā bhikkhū "
"bhikkhuniyo ovadantī’ti."
msgstr ""
"the senior monks aren’t instructing the nuns to render a service, but for "
"the sake of worldly gain?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs1.15"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs1.16a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="550"></a>
#. <span class="rule">
#. VAR: āmisahetu therā bhikkhū → āmisahetu bhikkhū (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs1.17"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu evaṃ vadeyya—‘āmisahetu therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovandantī’"
"ti, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk says that the senior monks are instructing the nuns for the sake "
"of worldly gain, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs1.18"
msgid "(<em>24</em>:<strong>73</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pc.24.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.24.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="551"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""
"… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order "
"through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.280"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="552"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs2.1.6"
msgid "Āmisahetūti"
msgstr "For the sake of worldly gain:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs2.1.7"
msgid ""
"cīvarahetu piṇḍapātahetu senāsanahetu gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārahetu "
"sakkārahetu garukārahetu mānanahetu vandanahetu pūjanahetu."
msgstr ""
"for the sake of robe-cloth, for the sake of almsfood, for the sake of a "
"dwelling, for the sake of medicines, for the sake of honor, for the sake of "
"respect, for the sake of deference, for the sake of veneration, for the sake "
"of worship."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="553"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs2.1.8"
msgid "Evaṃ vadeyyāti"
msgstr "Says:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs2.1.9"
msgid ""
"upasampannaṃ saṃghena sammataṃ bhikkhunovādakaṃ avaṇṇaṃ kattukāmo ayasaṃ "
"kattukāmo maṅkukattukāmo evaṃ vadeti—"
msgstr ""
"if, concerning one who is fully ordained and who has been agreed upon by the "
"Order as an instructor of nuns—desiring to disparage him, desiring to give "
"him a bad reputation, desiring to humiliate him—he says,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs2.1.10"
msgid ""
"“cīvarahetu piṇḍapātahetu senāsanahetu gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārahetu "
"sakkārahetu garukārahetu mānanahetu vandanahetu pūjanahetu ovadatī”ti "
"bhaṇati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"“He instructs for the sake of robe-cloth/for the sake of almsfood/for the "
"sake of a dwelling/for the sake of medicines/for the sake of honor/for the "
"sake of respect/for the sake of deference/for the sake of veneration/for the "
"sake of worship,” he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </span>
#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.24.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="554"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs2.2.1"
msgid "Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññī evaṃ vadeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a legitimate procedure, and he perceives it as legitimate, and he "
"says such a thing, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs2.2.2"
msgid "Dhammakamme vematiko evaṃ vadeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a legitimate procedure, but he is unsure if it is, and he says such "
"a thing, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs2.2.3"
msgid "Dhammakamme adhammakammasaññī evaṃ vadeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a legitimate procedure, but he perceives it as illegitimate, and he "
"says such a thing, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="555"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs2.2.4"
msgid ""
"Upasampannaṃ saṃghena asammataṃ bhikkhunovādakaṃ avaṇṇaṃ kattukāmo ayasaṃ "
"kattukāmo maṅkukattukāmo evaṃ vadeti—"
msgstr ""
"When someone who is fully ordained is an instructor of nuns, but he has not "
"been agreed upon by the Order as such, and a monk—desiring to disparage him, "
"desiring to give him a bad reputation, desiring to humiliate him—says,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs2.2.5"
msgid "“cīvarahetu … pe … pūjanahetu ovadatī”ti bhaṇati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"“He instructs for the sake of robe-cloth/for the sake of almsfood/for the "
"sake of a dwelling/for the sake of medicines/for the sake of honor/for the "
"sake of respect/for the sake of deference/for the sake of veneration/for the "
"sake of worship,” he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs2.2.6"
msgid ""
"Anupasampannaṃ saṃghena sammataṃ vā asammataṃ vā bhikkhunovādakaṃ avaṇṇaṃ "
"kattukāmo ayasaṃ kattukāmo maṅkukattukāmo evaṃ vadeti—"
msgstr ""
"When someone who is not fully ordained is an instructor of nuns, whether or "
"not he has been agreed upon by the Order as such, and a monk—desiring to "
"disparage him, desiring to give him a bad reputation, desiring to humiliate "
"him—says,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs2.2.7"
msgid ""
"“cīvarahetu piṇḍapātahetu senāsanahetu gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārahetu "
"sakkārahetu garukārahetu mānanahetu vandanahetu pūjanahetu ovadatī”ti "
"bhaṇati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"“He instructs for the sake of robe-cloth/for the sake of almsfood/for the "
"sake of a dwelling/for the sake of medicines/for the sake of honor/for the "
"sake of respect/for the sake of deference/for the sake of veneration/for the "
"sake of worship,” he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs2.2.8"
msgid "Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an illegitimate procedure, but he perceives it as legitimate, he "
"commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs2.2.9"
msgid "Adhammakamme vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an illegitimate procedure, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs2.2.10"
msgid "Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an illegitimate procedure, and he perceives it as illegitimate, he "
"commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.24.2.3"></a> <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.281"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="556"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs2.3.2"
msgid ""
"pakatiyā cīvarahetu piṇḍapātahetu senāsanahetu "
"gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārahetu sakkārahetu garukārahetu mānanahetu "
"vandanahetu pūjanahetu ovadantaṃ bhaṇati, ummattakassa, ādikammikassāti."
msgstr ""
"if he normally gives the instruction for the sake of robe-cloth/for the sake "
"of almsfood/for the sake of a dwelling/for the sake of medicines/for the "
"sake of honor/for the sake of respect/for the sake of deference/for the sake "
"of veneration/for the sake of worship;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs2.3.3"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs2.3.4"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="557"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc24:pts-cs2.3.5"
msgid "Āmisasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ."
msgstr "The fourth rule, the training rule on worldly gain, is finished."

